    <item>
      <title>Centromeric satellite background knowledge</title>
      <link>https://xscapintime.github.io/posts/centromeric_satellite_background/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 15 Jan 2024 10:40:02 -0500</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://xscapintime.github.io/posts/centromeric_satellite_background/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;chromosome-morphology&#34;&gt;Chromosome morphology &lt;a href=&#34;#chromosome-morphology&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;🔗&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;center&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;https://xscapintime.github.io/pics/17053334898727.jpg&#34; width=&#34;70%&#34; /&gt;&lt;/center&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Figure from&lt;sup id=&#34;fnref:1&#34;&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#fn:1&#34; class=&#34;footnote-ref&#34; role=&#34;doc-noteref&#34;&gt;1&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/sup&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;human-alpha-satellite-and-hor&#34;&gt;Human alpha satellite and HOR &lt;a href=&#34;#human-alpha-satellite-and-hor&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;🔗&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Alpha satellite: 171 bp&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;higher order repeat (HOR)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Live/active HOR&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Longer&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Higher Average methylation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hypomethylation dip for CENP binding&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dead/inactive HOR&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monors&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Available reference/annotation&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;T2T CHM13 (complete)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Censat track&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;center&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;pics/Screenshot 2024-01-15 at 11.04.24.png&#34; width=&#34;70%&#34; /&gt;&lt;/center&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Figure from&lt;sup id=&#34;fnref:2&#34;&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#fn:2&#34; class=&#34;footnote-ref&#34; role=&#34;doc-noteref&#34;&gt;2&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/sup&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;mouse-major-and-minor-satellite&#34;&gt;Mouse major and minor satellite &lt;a href=&#34;#mouse-major-and-minor-satellite&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;🔗&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Major satellite: 234 bp&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Minor satellite: 120 bp&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Available reference/annotation&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;mm39 (first 3.0 mb of each chromosome is empty)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;repeatmasker track&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;ref&#34;&gt;Ref. &lt;a href=&#34;#ref&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;🔗&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;footnotes&#34; role=&#34;doc-endnotes&#34;&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li id=&#34;fn:1&#34;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Potapova, Tamara A., and Jennifer L. Gerton. 2019. “Ribosomal DNA and the Nucleolus in the Context of Genome Organization.” Chromosome Research 27 (1): 109–27. &lt;a href=&#34;https://doi.org/10.1007/s10577-018-9600-5&#34;&gt;https://doi.org/10.1007/s10577-018-9600-5&lt;/a&gt;.&amp;#160;&lt;a href=&#34;#fnref:1&#34; class=&#34;footnote-backref&#34; role=&#34;doc-backlink&#34;&gt;&amp;#x21a9;&amp;#xfe0e;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li id=&#34;fn:2&#34;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Gershman, Ariel, Michael E. G. Sauria, Xavi Guitart, Mitchell R. Vollger, Paul W. Hook, Savannah J. Hoyt, Miten Jain, et al. 2022. “Epigenetic Patterns in a Complete Human Genome.” Science 376 (6588): eabj5089. &lt;a href=&#34;https://doi.org/10.1126/science.abj5089&#34;&gt;https://doi.org/10.1126/science.abj5089&lt;/a&gt;.&amp;#160;&lt;a href=&#34;#fnref:2&#34; class=&#34;footnote-backref&#34; role=&#34;doc-backlink&#34;&gt;&amp;#x21a9;&amp;#xfe0e;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
</description>
